# Typography

Three fonts are loaded via `next/font/google` in `layout.tsx` and exposed as CSS variables.

## Font Roles

| Role | Font | Variable | Weight | Size | Line Height | Color |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Headings (`h1`–`h6`) | Gelasio | `--font-heading` | 400 | — | 1.2 | `rgb(0,0,0)` |
| Subheadings | IBM Plex Sans | `--font-subheading` | 400 | 18px | 24px | `rgb(0,0,0)` |
| Body / paragraphs | Inter | `--font-body` | 300 | 14px | 18px | `rgba(0,0,0,0.75)` |

## Tailwind Utility Classes
```tsx
// Heading — Gelasio serif
<h2 className="font-heading text-4xl">...</h2>

// Subheading — IBM Plex Sans
<p className="font-subheading text-lg">...</p>

// Body — Inter light
<p className="font-body text-sm">...</p>
```

## Global CSS Application
- `h1`–`h6` → Gelasio 400 automatically via `globals.css`
- `p`, `li`, `td`, `blockquote` → Inter 300 automatically
- Apply `font-subheading` manually on labels, captions, or descriptive text

## DO NOT
- Do not use `font-sans` for headings — it resolves to Inter
- Do not set `font-weight: bold` on h-tags; Gelasio displays best at 400
- Do not override the base `p` color to full black; keep `rgba(0,0,0,0.75)`
